President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Mark Feierstein as Assistant Administrator for Latin America and the Caribbean at USAID and Osvaldo Gratacós as Inspector General at the Export-Import Bank of the United States. Feierstein is currently a principal and vice president at Greenberg Quinlan Rosner, an international polling firm. He has experience in public opinion research and has worked in various government positions, including at the U.S. Agency for International Development and the State Department. Gratacós is currently serving as the Acting Inspector General at the Export-Import Bank of the United States. He has previously worked as a commercial counsel at Motorola and as an attorney advisor for the U.S. Agency for International Development. Gratacós has also taught at the University of Virginia. Both nominees have impressive backgrounds and President Obama looks forward to working with them.